description: This C++ machine learning framework uses concepts, templates, and expression templates for efficient, modular neural network development. It supports matrix operations, layers (e.g., `weight_net_t`, `sigmoid_net_t`), optimizers (SGD, Adam, Nadam), and initialization methods (Xavier, He). Designed for performance and extensibility.

Github repository for the leakproof-ml tool. Also, contains as use example the results of the paper: "Leakproof ML: Data Leakage Prevention with a Robust, Interpretable, and Reproducible Machine Learning Framework"
This machine learning project provides a hybrid NLP framework for detecting Anxiety and Depression making early detection and prevention possible.

An interpretable machine learning framework for disentangling driving factors and depth-dependent precipitation thresholds of soil wetting in Chinas croplands. [JAG 2026]

A modular machine learning framework for battery dataset classification and RUL prediction.

This project presents a comprehensive Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) framework for early heart disease risk prediction. Unlike traditional black-box machine learning models, this system emphasizes interpretability, temporal risk evolution, fairness, uncertainty awareness, and clinical decision support.
a dataset combined of historical and behavioral data used to power a hybrid framework using deep machine learning.

A comprehensive and extensible ontology for systematically modeling fairness notions, metrics, biases, evaluation methods, and scientific provenance in machine learning. This ontology provides researchers, developers, and practitioners with a unified, machine-readable framework to guide the design and assessment of fair ML systems.

MLForge is an open-source, modular machine learning framework written in C++ that provides a robust foundation for developing, testing, and benchmarking a variety of machine learning algorithms. Its design emphasizes clarity, efficiency, and flexibilitymaking it a powerful tool for both educational and prototyping purposes.
Demographic-aware machine learning framework for QoE prediction in 5G video streaming using classical ML and TabNet deep learning models with dataset augmentation.
Planter is a modular framework for realising in one-click in-network machine learning algorithms.

A curated collection of advanced satellite image analysis projects, frameworks, and tools  focused on reconstruction, enhancement, interpretation, and machine learning workflows for remote sensing data.

Cerebrus is an intelligent malware analysis framework designed to provide multi-layered defense against modern cyber threats. It integrates static analysis, machine learning, external threat intelligence, and explainable AI (XAI) to deliver a robust platform for detecting known and unknown malware across various file formats.

"A machine learning framework for the automated detection and localization of sensor anomalies in commercial aircraft, leveraging the NASA DASHlink aviation dataset for enhanced flight safety and predictive maintenance."

BioGraphX is a comprehensive framework for extracting biophysical features from protein sequences using graph-theoretical approaches. The system models proteins as interaction networks where residues form nodes and biochemical interactions form edges, enabling sophisticated feature extraction for downstream machine learning applications

A machine learning framework, dataset and research sub-module about coevolutionary planetary intelligence dynamics. This project explores how nurturing its emergent patterns may lead to a synergistic increase in the overall capability and intelligence of both individual agents and the collective system.

A distributed machine learning framework designed for real-world edge deployments where devices are resource-constrained, connections are unreliable and trust cannot be assumed. Built in Rust from the ground up, it brings swarm intelligence and federated learning primitives to environments where PyTorch and TensorFlow cannot operate.

Combines TF-IDF, transformer embeddings (MiniLM), and ensemble models (Logistic Regression, XGBoost, MLP) to predict hierarchical product categories with strong F1 performance.

Heart disease is a leading cause of mortality, making early diagnosis crucial. Traditional methods are time-consuming and costly, but machine learning (ML) can improve accuracy and efficiency. TensorFlow is an open-source deep learning framework developed by Google. It helps build, train, and deploy machine-learning models using tensors and data-flow graphs. TensorFlow supports neural networks, GPU/TPU acceleration, automatic differentiation, and is widely used in AI applications like image recognition and NLP.

This repository contains machine learning models and loss functions implemented from scratch using NumPy. The goal is to understand the core mathematics behind ML algorithms without relying on high-level frameworks.

This project develops an AI-driven framework to enhance noise resilience and optimize application-oriented quantum computing in the NISQ era. By integrating machine learning for error mitigation, circuit optimization, and hybrid quantum-classical workflows, it enables reliable, practical quantum solutions within current hardware limitations.

This project analyzes time-varying volatility in financial markets using a GARCH(1,1) framework and compares it with machine-learningbased volatility estimation. The study focuses on volatility clustering, regime behavior, and model robustness across calm and stress periods rather than return prediction.
